"""
Substrate Fingerprint Atlas — Phase δ.

Three tests:
  1. Cheap-fingerprint discrimination — does a subset of cheap slots
     distinguish all 6 fixtures?
  2. Redesigned slot 16 (channel_spread_log10) — orthogonal to slot 13?
  3. Near-miss robustness — perturbed-window SR cheap fingerprint
     still closest to canonical SR?

This phase shifts focus from slot design to slot USE — the user's
strategic frame: "scan a barcode, identify the surface trivially."

Preregistry: Build_Docs/Reports/substrate_fingerprint_atlas_phase_delta/preregistry.md
"""
